# Roberts' Domain Modeling Example
# Category: scholars
# Description: Complex domain model with inheritance and multiple relations
# Source: Roberts (1973) "The Existential Graphs of Charles S. Peirce"
# Pattern: domain_modeling

# "Every professor is a person who teaches courses and has students"
# ∀x(Professor(x) → (Person(x) ∧ ∃y(Course(y) ∧ Teaches(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(Student(z) ∧ Has(x,z))))
*x ~[ (Professor x) ~[ (Person x) *y (Course y) (Teaches x y) *z (Student z) (Has x z) ] ]
